<task id="R7-090" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Audit SessionSummarizeOrchestrator caller graph; design Path A.5 migration</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>9</wave>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>audit, bff-api, wave-9</tags>
    <rigor-level>STANDARD</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>024</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-17 (audit + design portion)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wave 9 starts here. Before refactoring SessionSummarizeOrchestrator (task 091), audit the
    current caller graph and the existing partial migration that chat-routing-redesign-r1 left in
    place. Today the orchestrator already uses IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync but still
    dispatches through IPlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync (a streaming-specific
    method), NOT through the canonical IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync triangle that ADR-013
    mandates. R7 FR-17 closes this gap. Produce a clean Path A.5 migration design doc so task 091
    can execute without re-reading source.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer familiar with the Spaarke BFF AI architecture, the canonical
    IInvokePlaybookAi triangle (ADR-013), and the IConsumerRoutingService 5-min TTL cache (ADR-014).
    Goal: extract the right migration path, not re-implement.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A migration-design document at
    `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/chat-summarize-migration-design.md`
    that answers:
    1. What is the current SessionSummarizeOrchestrator caller graph? (Who calls it, who does it call?)
    2. What is the gap between today's IPlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync path and
       the canonical IInvokePlaybookAi triangle (ADR-013)?
    3. What is the Path A.5 design:
       IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync("chat-summarize") -> playbook ID ->
       IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync(playbookId, payload)?
    4. What streaming-vs-non-streaming semantics must be preserved (Structured Outputs streaming +
       IncrementalJsonParser field-delta emission)?
    5. What sprk_playbookconsumer row needs to exist (FR-17 acceptance criterion handled in task 092)?
    6. What is the fallback behavior (graceful-degrade if routing-table returns null) the design
       must preserve from chat-routing-redesign-r1 task 028d?
    7. What integration test confirms the end-to-end migration works (chat /summarize works
       through playbook dispatch)?
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-doc">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="refactor-target">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs</file>
    <file purpose="canonical-triangle">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/IInvokePlaybookAi.cs</file>
    <file purpose="canonical-triangle-impl">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/InvokePlaybookAi.cs</file>
    <file purpose="legacy-direct-path">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs</file>
    <file purpose="chat-endpoints">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs</file>
    <file purpose="consumer-routing-doc">docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — IInvokePlaybookAi triangle is canonical. SessionSummarizeOrchestrator MUST route through this triangle post-R7, not through IPlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync (chat-streaming-specific).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Caching — IConsumerRoutingService 5-min TTL is preserved verbatim. NFR-04: invalidation hook is NOT in R7 scope.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-17">Migrate chat-summarize from legacy direct path (AnalysisOrchestrationService.ExecuteAnalysisAsync) to playbook dispatch via IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync + IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-04">Consumer routing cache invalidation hook NOT in R7 scope — design must not propose new invalidation logic.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Audit task — modification justification triple applies to task 091 (the refactor task), not this audit.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Audit task does not modify BFF; no publish-size check needed for this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="MUST NOT modify">docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md — READ-ONLY in R7 per spec (chat-routing-redesign-r1 owns).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>ai/consumer-routing</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-013-bff-ai-architecture.md</file>
