    <patterns>
      <pattern name="IInvokePlaybookAi triangle (canonical)" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/IInvokePlaybookAi.cs">
        ADR-013 canonical AI public contract. SessionSummarizeOrchestrator (post-R7) and every
        consumer-routed dispatch path MUST flow through this triangle.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="DailyBriefingEndpoints /narrate case study" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/DailyBriefingEndpoints.cs:201-374">
        Reference impl of "consumer code -> IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync -> IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync" pattern.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      chat-routing-redesign-r1 task 028d landed a partial migration: SessionSummarizeOrchestrator
      now consults IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync(ConsumerTypes.ChatSummarize) for the
      playbook ID, falling back to WorkspaceOptions.ChatSummarizePlaybookId when the routing-table
      returns null. But the dispatch step still calls IPlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync
      directly (a streaming-specific method) instead of going through the canonical
      IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync triangle that ADR-013 mandates. This is the gap R7 FR-17 closes.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="024" status="must-be-complete">PlaybookOrchestrationService.ExecuteNodeAsync single-hop dispatch must be ready so task 091 can build on a stable orchestrator surface.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>chat-routing-redesign-r1 task 028d — landed partial routing-table consultation; R7 FR-17 completes the migration to the canonical triangle.</item>
      <item>R7 task 092 (this wave) — adds the chat-summarize row to sprk_playbookconsumer table.</item>
      <item>R7 task 042 (Wave 4) DEPENDS on this wave completing — cannot delete ExecuteAnalysisAsync until chat-summarize is fully migrated.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: audit-only task, no source modification, planning artifact only · Proceeding with Step 0...
