      Read the full source file. Note: how IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync is called today,
      how IPlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync is dispatched, where streaming chunks emit.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read IInvokePlaybookAi canonical surface">
      Read IInvokePlaybookAi.cs + InvokePlaybookAi.cs. Document the method signature, payload shape,
      return shape, and how it relates to PlaybookOrchestrationService.ExecuteAsync.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Read DailyBriefingEndpoints reference impl">
      Read DailyBriefingEndpoints.cs:201-374 for the canonical "consumer -> routing -> InvokePlaybookAi" wiring.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Read AnalysisOrchestrationService.ExecuteAnalysisAsync">
      Read the legacy direct-invocation path that R7 deletes (FR-11). Confirm no remaining caller in
      SessionSummarizeOrchestrator post-task-091.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Identify integration-test entry points">
      Grep for tests under tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionSummarizeOrchestrator*.cs
      to identify what test scaffold exists for task 091's integration test acceptance.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Read ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md (READ-ONLY)">
      Note: do NOT modify. Just confirm the documented routing pattern matches the design.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Write migration-design document">
      Create `notes/spikes/chat-summarize-migration-design.md` answering the 7 goal questions.
      Include code-snippet sketches of the before/after dispatch sites (target: 120-180 lines).
      Explicitly state: streaming-vs-non-streaming preservation strategy + the integration-test plan.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
